$ PowerShell: the preference variable $psDefaultParameterValues

The → Windows/PowerShell preference variable `$psDefaultParameterValues` is a → Windows/PowerShell/language/type/hash-table, that is: it stores key/value pairs.

{ Format of keys and values

  The format of the keys in in `$psDefaultParameterValues` is `cmdletName:parameterName`. Both, `cmdletName` and `parameterName` can contain wildcard characters.

  A value is either the string `defaultValue` or a → Windows/PowerShell/language/scriptblock.

}
